snippet.title: The Devil Wears Prada 2 | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
Everybody wants this. 

Meryl Streep, Anne Hathaway, Emily Blunt, and Stanley Tucci return in The Devil Wears Prada 2, in theaters May 1. Watch the full trailer now. 

Almost 20 years after making their iconic turn as Miranda, Andy, Emily and Nigel—Meryl Streep, Anne Hathaway, Emily Blunt and Stanley Tucci return to the fashionable streets of New York City and the sleek offices of Runway Magazine in the eagerly awaited sequel to the 2006 phenomenon that defined a generation. 
 
The film reunites the original main cast with director David Frankel and writer Aline Brosh McKenna, and introduces an all-new runway of characters including Kenneth Branagh, Simone Ashley, Justin Theroux, Lucy Liu, Patrick Brammall, Caleb Hearon, Helen J. Shen, Pauline Chalamet, B.J. Novak and Conrad Ricamora. Tracie Thoms and Tibor Feldman also reprise their roles as “Lily” and “Irv” from the first film. 
 
“The Devil Wears Prada 2” is produced by Wendy Finerman, and executive produced by Michael Bederman, Karen Rosenfelt and Aline Brosh McKenna. The film debuts exclusively in theaters May 1.

snippet.title: Character Trailer - "Zibai: Mortal Flesh to Kindred Earth" | Genshin Impact #GenshinImpact #Zibai
snippet.description:
The Three Deadly Selves as specters come. In union born, in union quelled.
To hold a day as a passing year, illuminate the heart that was.
Singer: Alan

English Translation:
The moon, a jade plate, climbs the misty skies
Thin dewdrops gleam as they fall like sighs
Which grass shall never yellow in the fleeting day?
Which virtue lasts while seasons slip away?
Like drifting dust along the country way
The grass lies pale, the poplars sere, yet the end delays
By the roadside, the remnants keep their rites
As bronze statues of old lie lost in thorn and briar
All things keep their seasons, past all mortal measure
Passing through this mortal world like a waking dream
Like drifting shadows, fleeting, swift, and bright
Time races on, a white steed through the desolate plain
Its path unknown, its destination unseen
Which grass shall never yellow in the fleeting day?
Which virtue lasts while seasons slip away?
Like drifting dust along the country way
Alone with my staff, I cross the river on a single reed, like a lone wild goose in flight
Who says the river is too wide to cross?
Through shadowed reeds I seek the broken jade
The past cannot be undone, the road ahead stretches long
Friends spread the mat and share their wine, while distant fields of millet sway and shine
Some till the soil, some sow the seed — this is the life the people long to lead
In desolate courts, the withered grass sways in the moon's pale beam, and waning decay glimmers as fireflies' dream

Passing through this mortal world like a waking dream
Like drifting shadows, fleeting, swift, and bright
Time races on, a white steed through the desolate plain
Its path unknown, its destination unseen
Which grass shall never yellow in the fleeting day?
Which virtue lasts while seasons slip away?
Like drifting dust along the country way
Alone with my staff, I cross the river on a single reed, like a lone wild goose in flight
Who says the river is too wide to cross?
Through shadowed reeds I seek the broken jade
The past cannot be undone, the road ahead stretches long
Friends spread the mat and share their wine, while distant fields of millet sway and shine
Some till the soil, some sow the seed — this is the life the people long to lead
In desolate courts, the withered grass sways in the moon's pale beam, and waning decay glimmers as fireflies' dream
